+   executor (execute_cmd.c) -- the dominant uncovered surface.
+
+   The remedy is the sanctioned single-run equivalent of "pin input A, run;
+   pin input B, run; merge": pin the symbolic stdin to ONE OF A MENU of
+   complete, valid bash programs, selected by a symbolic klee_range.  KLEE
+   forks once on the selector and explores EVERY program in a SINGLE run, so
+   the coverage is one manifest.json / one eval-transformations invocation,
+   never a cross-run profraw union.  Each program ends in "\nexit\n" so the
+   top-level `exit' builtin terminates the state BEFORE the parser reaches
+   the still-symbolic tail bytes after the pin -- which is what keeps the
+   front-end fork explosion from coming back.  klee_assume records the bytes
+   on the symbolic stdin object (so the native coverage binary replays that
