+     count byte-identical (so bfs keeps emitting 8 ktests) and only enrich the two
+     entries that actually emit, as supersets that PRESERVE their unique builtins
+     and ADD more within the 100-byte --sym-stdin cap. e2 += `hash -r;type -ta cd`;
+     e6 += `times;let x=7%3`. Oracle union 15,567 -> 15,684 (+117); both repacked
+     entries verified <=100 bytes and exit-clean. NOTE the 100-byte cap is the
+     binding budget: the densest single <=100B program covers ~7k lines, and the
+     repack only nets +117 distinct union over v7 because the high-yield surface is
+     already claimed by other entries -- itself evidence the source axis is near
